Fermat's Principle \(
ewcommand{ m}{\mathbf}
ewcommand{\dd}{\mathrm{d}}
ewcommand{\pp}{\partial}\) Fermat's Principle is $$\delta s=\delta\int n\dd \ell=0$$ If we choose the path connecting two points to be $$ m r= m r(t),\quad t_0\leq t\leq t_1$$ We can write $$s=\int n rac{\dd \ell}{\dd t}\dd t, \quad  rac{\dd \ell}{\dd t}=|\dot{ m r}|$$ The Lagrangian about parameter \(t\) is $$L=n rac{\dd \ell}{\dd t}=n( m r)| m{\dot r}|$$ then the Euler-Lagrange Equation is $$ egin{aligned} &\left( rac{\dd}{\dd t} rac{\pp}{\pp m{\dot r}}- rac{\pp}{\pp m{r}}ight)L=0\  m p&= rac{\pp L}{\pp  m{\dot r}}=n \hat	au,\quad\hat{	au}= rac{\pp |\dot{ m r}|}{\pp  m{\dot r}}= m{\dot r}/| m{\dot r}|= rac{\dd m r}{\dd\ell}\  rac{\dd  m p}{\dd t}&= rac{\pp L}{\pp  m{r}}= rac{\dd\ell}{\dd t}
abla n\  rac{\dd  m p}{\dd \ell}&=
abla n= m F\end{aligned}$$ Generalized Momentum \( m p\) is independent of the choice of \(t\) , and Examples Rectangular Coordinates $$n(x,y,z)=f(x,y),\quad m F= rac{\pp f}{\pp x}\hat x+ rac{\pp f}{\pp y}\hat y$$ It is obvious that \(p_z\) are conserved. Central Gradient Define \( m L= m r	imes  m p\) , $$ egin{aligned}  rac{\dd  m L}{\dd \ell}&= rac{\dd m r}{\dd \ell}	imes m p+ m r	imes rac{\dd m p}{\dd \ell} \&=\hat{	au}	imes  m p+ m r	imes m F \&= m r	imes m F\end{aligned}$$ \( m L\) is conserved for a spherical symmetric distribution $$n( m r)=f(r),\quad  m r	imes m F= m 0$$ \(L_z\) is conserved for $$n( m r)=f(r,	heta),\quad ( m r	imes m F)_z=0$$ if (!document.getElementById('mathjaxscript_pelican_#%@#$@#')) { var align = "center", indent = "0em", linebreak = "false"; if (false) { align = (screen.width < 768) ? "left" : align; indent = (screen.width < 768) ? "0em" : indent; linebreak = (screen.width < 768) ? 'true' : linebreak; } var mathjaxscript = document.createElement('script'); mathjaxscript.id = 'mathjaxscript_pelican_#%@#$@#'; mathjaxscript.type = 'text/javascript'; mathjaxscript.src = 'https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/mathjax/2.7.3/latest.js?config=TeX-AMS-MML_HTMLorMML'; mathjaxscript[(window.opera ? "innerHTML" : "text")] = "MathJax.Hub.Config({" + " config: ['MMLorHTML.js']," + " TeX: { extensions: ['AMSmath.js','AMSsymbols.js','noErrors.js','noUndefined.js'], equationNumbers: { autoNumber: 'AMS' } }," + " jax: ['input/TeX','input/MathML','output/HTML-CSS']," + " extensions: ['tex2jax.js','mml2jax.js','MathMenu.js','MathZoom.js']," + " displayAlign: '"+ align +"'," + " displayIndent: '"+ indent +"'," + " showMathMenu: true," + " messageStyle: 'normal'," + " tex2jax: { " + " inlineMath: [ ['\\(','\\)'] ], " + " displayMath: [ ['$$','$$'] ]," + " processEscapes: true," + " preview: 'TeX'," + " }, " + " 'HTML-CSS': { " + " styles: { '.MathJax_Display, .MathJax .mo, .MathJax .mi, .MathJax .mn': {color: 'inherit ! important'} }," + " linebreaks: { 